data.description: Located in the charming Gallatin Gateway area, this 1733 sq ft home features 3 bedrooms and 2 baths with a 10x12 storage shed.  A rural like setting with no HOA and light covenants allows you to bring your horses.  There is an insulated tack shed and horse shelter that was added in 2017 ready for use along with one water trough and the saddle racks staying to make it truly horse ready.  This remarkable property situated just off of Highway 191 and Gooch Hill Road encompasses almost 1 acre and is centrally located whether you are headed towards Big Sky or into the Bozeman area.  Numerous updates in the home make this a great value with the opportunity to create your own private ranch haven while still being in a wonderful neighborhood.  The community of Gallatin Gateway is one of the older settlements in Gallatin County and had its beginnings in the 1860's.  Despite rapid growth to the area, the community has been able to hold onto many elements of its historic past.  Proximity to the Gallatin River, Stacey's Bar, The Jump and numerous hiking and riding trails all combine to make this property one not to miss.  Schedule your showing today.
